OPA provides a REST API to:

    Load Policies: Upload policies that define what is allowed (allow) or denied.
    Query Policies: Send input data to OPA and get policy decisions (e.g., allow/deny).
    Test Policies: Validate that policies behave as expected using test inputs.


We defined authentication.rego

Then:
docker run -d --name opa -p 8181:8181 openpolicyagent/opa:latest run --server

then loaded the policy:
curl -X PUT http://localhost:8181/v1/policies/authentication \
--data-binary @authentication.rego


Verified the locad:
curl http://localhost:8181/v1/policies


Use this value for the expiration below (current time plus 300 seconds):
echo $(( $(date +%s) + 300 ))

And querried the policy:
curl -X POST http://localhost:8181/v1/data/security/authentication \
-H "Content-Type: application/json" \
-d '{
    "input": {
        "token": {
            "payload": {
                "sub": "testuser",
                "exp": 1734472090
            }
        }
    }
}'
